President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Arkansas due to severe storms and straight-line winds that occurred on April 12, 2020. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Roland Jackson has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.